block content
    .main-aside-container
        .main-news-block
            .infoblock
                .infoblock__item
                    h1 About Us

                    p U.Today is a global media organisation dedicated to helping you understand the new generation tech and the future it brings to society.

                    p Our mission is to serve the emerging community of enthusiasts, professionals and newcomers who explore, use and develop the tech by heeding the core journalistic values of clear thinking, accuracy and independence.

                    p We seek to inform, educate, collaborate and support better practices for the benefit of all.

                .infoblock__item
                    h2 Terms & policies

                    ul
                        li
                            a(href="https://u.today/terms-and-conditions" target="_blank") Terms & Conditions

                        li
                            a(href="https://u.today/consent-settings" target="_blank") Consent Settings

                        li
                            a(href="https://u.today/privacy-policy" target="_blank") Privacy Policy

                        li
                            a(href="https://u.today/editorial-policy" target="_blank") Editorial Policy

                        li
                            a(href="https://u.today/cookie" target="_blank") Cookie Policy

                .infoblock__item
                    h2 Business Information

                    p <strong>Our address:</strong> 111395, Moscow, Moldagulova Street, Building 10, 2

                    p <strong>For donations:</strong>

                    ul
                        li Official U.Today BTC wallet: 1EXCmnrTvohJwzymCufkLqw6zVrNvhApQN <br>

                        li Official U.Today ETH wallet: 0x66B4157a5180F22DF948A01CFD6106dd0076f08d

                .infoblock__item
                    h2 Corrections or feedback?

                    p If a story contains inaccuracies or breaches of our ethical code, please reach out to our editor by email: <a href="mailto:editor@u.today">editor@u.today</a>

                    p If a story has been corrected and a grave error has been made by U.today, the correction and explanation will be published under the category U.today Apology.

